# Notification System

## Architecture overview

Notifications flow through a chain of files. Every new notification type must touch each layer:

```
Shared schemas  ->  Text generation  ->  Helper function  ->  NotificationService
                                                                    |
                                                              in_app + email
                                                                    |
                                                          Email template mapper
                                                                    |
                                                        React Email component
```

## Chain of files (in order)

| Step | File | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| 1 | `packages/shared/src/schemas/notifications.ts` | Zod metadata schema, actions schema, and full notification schema |
| 2 | `packages/shared/src/utils/notification-text.ts` | `generateNotificationText()` switch case for title/description |
| 3 | `apps/backend/src/services/notifications/helpers.ts` | Helper function that calls `service.createNotification()` |
| 4 | `packages/transactional/emails/{name}-email.tsx` | React Email template component |
| 5 | `packages/transactional/src/email-templates.ts` | `getEmailTemplate()` switch case mapping type to component |
| 6 | `packages/transactional/src/index.ts` | Export the template and its props type |

## Adding a new notification type

### Step 1: Database migration

Add the new type to the `notification_type` enum in a migration:

```sql
ALTER TYPE notification_type ADD VALUE IF NOT EXISTS 'my_new_type';
```

Then regenerate DB types: `cd apps/backend && pnpm generate:db`

### Step 2: Shared metadata schema (`packages/shared/src/schemas/notifications.ts`)

Define three schemas and add them to the discriminated unions:

```typescript
// 1. Metadata schema
export const MyNewTypeMetadataSchema = z.object({
  type: z.literal('my_new_type'),
  // ... type-specific fields
});

// 2. Actions schema
export const MyNewTypeActionsSchema = z
  .array(BaseActionSchema.extend({
    type: z.literal('view_something'),
    label: z.string(),
    url: z.url().optional(),
  }))
  .nullable();

// 3. Full notification schema
export const MyNewTypeNotificationSchema = BaseNotificationSchema.extend({
  type: z.literal('my_new_type'),
  metadata: MyNewTypeMetadataSchema,
  actions: MyNewTypeActionsSchema,
});
```

Add the metadata schema to `NotificationMetadataSchema` (discriminated union) and the full schema to `NotificationSchema`.

### Step 3: Text generation (`packages/shared/src/utils/notification-text.ts`)

Add a case in `generateNotificationText()`:

```typescript
case 'my_new_type': {
  const meta = metadata as TypedNotificationMetadata<'my_new_type'>;
  return {
    title: 'Titulo en espanol',
    description: `Descripcion con ${meta.someField}`,
  };
}
```

### Step 4: Notification helper (`apps/backend/src/services/notifications/helpers.ts`)

Create a helper function:

```typescript
export async function notifyMyNewType(
  service: NotificationService,
  params: { userId: string; /* ... */ },
) {
  return await service.createNotification({
    userId: params.userId,
    type: 'my_new_type',
    channels: ['in_app', 'email'], // or ['in_app'] for in-app only
    actions: [{ type: 'view_something', label: 'Ver', url: `${APP_BASE_URL}/...` }],
    metadata: { type: 'my_new_type', /* ... */ },
  });
}
```

### Step 5: Email template (skip if in-app only)

Create `packages/transactional/emails/my-new-type-email.tsx`:

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import {Button, Section, Text} from '@react-email/components';
import {BaseEmail} from './base-template';

export interface MyNewTypeEmailProps {
  someField: string;
  actionUrl: string;
  appBaseUrl?: string;
}

export const MyNewTypeEmail = ({someField, actionUrl, appBaseUrl}: MyNewTypeEmailProps) => (
  <BaseEmail title="Email title" preview="Preview text" appBaseUrl={appBaseUrl}>
    <Text className="text-foreground mb-4">Content with {someField}.</Text>
    <Section className="text-center mb-6">
      <Button
        href={actionUrl}
        className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-6 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold text-base no-underline inline-block"
      >
        Call to action
      </Button>
    </Section>
  </BaseEmail>
);

MyNewTypeEmail.PreviewProps = { someField: 'example', actionUrl: '#' } as MyNewTypeEmailProps;
export default MyNewTypeEmail;
```

### Step 6: Email template mapper (`packages/transactional/src/email-templates.ts`)

Add import and switch case in `getEmailTemplate()`:

```typescript
// Import
import {
  MyNewTypeEmail as MyNewTypeEmailComponent,
  type MyNewTypeEmailProps,
} from '../emails/my-new-type-email';

// In switch statement
case 'my_new_type': {
  const meta = metadata as TypedNotificationMetadata<'my_new_type'>;
  return {
    Component: MyNewTypeEmailComponent,
    props: { someField: meta?.someField, actionUrl: '...', appBaseUrl } as MyNewTypeEmailProps,
  };
}
```

For **in-app only** types (no email), add them to the throw block instead:

```typescript
case 'my_inapp_only_type':
  throw new Error(`Notification type ${notificationType} is in_app only and does not have an email template`);
```

### Step 7: Export from transactional package (`packages/transactional/src/index.ts`)

```typescript
export * from '../emails/my-new-type-email';
export type {MyNewTypeEmailProps} from '../emails/my-new-type-email';
```

## Channels

- `in_app` - Stored in DB, shown in the notification bell UI. Always "sent" on creation.
- `email` - Rendered via React Email and sent through email provider (Resend). Requires a template in `packages/transactional/emails/`.

When adding `email` channel, the type **must** have a case in `getEmailTemplate()`. Otherwise it hits the `default` branch and throws "Unknown notification type".

## Key patterns

- **Fire-and-forget**: Helpers are called with `.catch()` so notification failures don't break the main flow
- **Deferred jobs**: Use `deferSendToJob: true` for heavy emails (attachments, invoices). The cronjob picks them up.
- **Debounced notifications**: Use `createDebouncedNotification()` to batch rapid notifications (e.g. multiple document uploads) into one
- **Metadata validation**: `NotificationService` validates metadata against the Zod schema before storing. Invalid metadata throws `ValidationError`.
- **Text from metadata**: Title and description are generated from metadata via `generateNotificationText()`, not stored directly.

## Existing notification types by channel

**in_app + email**: `order_confirmed`, `order_expired`, `payment_failed`, `document_reminder`, `document_uploaded`, `ticket_sold_seller`, `payout_completed`, `payout_failed`, `payout_cancelled`, `seller_earnings_retained`, `buyer_ticket_cancelled`, `ticket_report_created`, `ticket_report_action_added`, `ticket_report_closed`, auth types

**in_app only**: `identity_verification_failed`, `identity_verification_manual_review`, `ticket_report_status_changed`

